.TH PlayTag "1.00" "May 2018" "GNU coreutils 8.25" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
PlayTag \- create or modify m3u playlist
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B PlayTag
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Allows you to choose between creating new playlist based on tags, modifing existed playlist or modifing tags of existing mp3 file.
.PP
There are no mandatory arguments.
Whole interaction with script is based on graphical interface called Zenity.
The only available paremeters are:
.TP
\fB\-h\fR
shows help page
.TP
\fB\-v\fR
shows information about current version and author
.PP
It is essential to have mp3info addon installed before using this script.
You can do this by your own or through the script (there is an option at the very beginning).
.PP
First menu gives you three options:
.PP
1. Create playlist
.PP
2. Modify playlist
.PP
3. Modify mp3 tags of a single mp3 file
.PP
Depending on your choice there will appeare next window.
.PP
For creating a playlist it will be menu which allows you to set parameters to find exactly wanted files to store in your newly created playlist.
After setting criteria you will be asked for choosing directory to save the playlist and for choosing its name.
.PP
For second option you will have to select playlist to edit.
Then the menu with songs will appear.
You will be able to delete songs (from paylist) by clicking on them or adding new by choosing right option form the list.
After all you can save you changes by selecting the 'Zapisz' option.
.PP
If you chose third option you will have to select mp3 file to edit.
In the new menu you need to write only this options that you want to change, the rest will stay untouched.
